Approach 1- simple string operation. if the current element = top element (back) of the string, pop it, else push
TC- O(N) SC- O(N)

class Solution {
public:
    string removeDuplicates(string s) {
        string temp = "";
        for(char c : s){
            if(!temp.empty() && temp.back() == c) temp.pop_back();
            else temp.push_back(c);
        }
        return temp;
    }
};

OPtimised approach- using 2 pointers and treating them like stack so theres O(1) SC
treat i as the top of the stack and j to scan the string.
push operation => s[i] = s[j] and i++;
pop operation- i -= 2;

string removeDuplicates(string s) {
    int i = 0;

    for (int j = 0; j < s.size(); j++) {
        s[i] = s[j];
        if (i > 0 && s[i] == s[i - 1]) {
            i -= 2;
        }
        i++;
    }

    return s.substr(0, i);
}

